Source.Name: httpd
Source.Summary: A secure, standards-compliant, efficient and extensible HTTP server.
Source.Description:
Produced via a collaborative software development effort aimed at creating a robust, commercial-grade, featureful, and freely-available source code implementation of an HTTP (Web) server.
Based on the the public domain HTTP daemon devloped by Rob McCool at the National Center for Supercomputing Applications (NCSA), University of Illonois, Urbana-Champaign.
